$ Shell command: nload
@ nload

`nload` displays the current network usage.

code {
$ nload _device_
code }

Find available devices with
code {
$ → Linux/shell/commands/nmcli#nmcli-d-status[nmcli device status]
$ ip link show
code }

sa:

  Other → Linux/shell/commands[shell commands] such as `iftop`, `nethogs`, `speedometer` (a Python script), `bmon` (the `b` stands for bandwith).
